+    accept worker credentials per 12a-1 §D.5. Authority rules:
+    - `acquire_lease`: caller MUST be in the `orchestrators`
+      group; `holder` field MUST equal the authenticated
+      `worker_id` (no impersonation).
+    - `renew_lease`: caller MUST be the lease's current
+      `holder`.
+    - `release_lease`: caller MUST be the lease's current
+      `holder`.
+    - `register_experiment` / `unregister_experiment`:
+      admin-token only.
+    - `list_experiments` / `read_experiment_metadata`:
+      authenticated worker (any group) OR admin-token.
+    This preserves 12a-2's worker-credential model: the
+    orchestrator boots with the admin token (to register
+    itself + join `orchestrators`) but uses its own worker
+    credential for ongoing lease ops.
